content: Engaged in an online forum for quant traders. Shared some insights from my recent strategies. Got positive feedback and an invitation to a closed group.
Went on a date. It was refreshing to talk about life outside of code and markets. Maybe a balance is what I need to keep my focus sharp.
Participated in a hackathon organized by a DeFi startup. Our team didn't win, but I learned a ton about real-world applications of blockchain.
My mentor introduced me to his colleague at the quant firm. We had an informal interview over lunch. They're looking for someone to lead a project. Hopeful.
Revisited my trading strategies. Incorporating some lessons from Japan—patience and resilience. Adjusted parameters based on new insights.
Joined a Solana meetup. The energy here is incredible. Connected with developers, got advice on my smart contract, and even found a potential collaborator.
Just got a call back for a follow-up interview at the quant firm. My strategy integration with Rust has piqued their interest. The journey continues, with NYC as my backdrop.
